r an Indian student is as follows:</p>\r\n          \r\n<table class=\"table table-responsive\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Entrance Exam in India</td>\r\n<td>There is no entrance exam in India like IELTS/SAT, etc. NEET qualification is a must.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Age</td>\r\n<td>The student must be at least 17 years old as on 31st December of the year in which the admission is being taken.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Board</td>\r\n<td>The candidate must have completed class 12th from a regular and recognised board.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Marks in class 12th</td>\r\n<td>The student must have 50% marks individually in Physics, Chemistry and Biology in class 12th. The student must have studied Physics, Chemistry, Biology and English as compulsory subjects in 11th and 12th. The board should be a recognised one.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>NEET</td>\r\n<td>You need to qualify NEET for admission in any MCI recognised medical university in Ukraine. NEET is valid for 3 years from 2018 onwards.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Passport</td>\r\n<td>The student must hold a valid passport.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">Note:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n<li style=\"text-align: left;\" aria-level=\"1\">At the time of applying for admission letter, it is not necessary to have a passport. Admission letter can be issued if the student has a valid id proof such as Aadhar card. However, for the invitation letter and for the visa, a valid passport is required.</li>\r\n<li style=\"text-align: left;\" aria-level=\"1\">Admission is not possible in VNMU if the student has not qualified NEET.</li>\r\n</ul>', '<p>Vinnitsa National Medical University is recognised by the following:<br>\r\n● The Medical Council of India (MCI)<br>\r\n● World Health Organisation (WHO)<br>\r\n● ECFMG<br>\r\n● Medical Board of California<br>\r\n● Education Ministry of Ukraine</p>\r\n<p>This means that you can appear for the licensing exams in countries such as India, USA, UK etc., after graduating from VNMU.</p>\r\n', '', '', 1, 1),
(2, 2, 'PUBLIC', 'M.D. PHYSICIAN', 'ENGLISH', '6 YEARS', '5000$', '<p><strong>Ternopil National Medical University</strong>&nbsp;is a medical university in Ukraine. It was founded on September 1, 1957. It is one of the best medical universities in Ukraine, ranking third among the higher medical schools according to IV (fourth) highest level of accreditation by the Ministry of Health and education of Ukraine. It is composed of national and international students. The number of foreign students studying currently in school is about 800 from 48 different countries all over the world. Ternopil State Medical University is ranked 13060 out of 20,000 universities in the world by Webometrics World University ranking and ranked at 8854 out of 11,000 universities in the world by 4icu world university ranking.</p>\r\n<p><i>Before April 2019, the university was known as Ternopil State Medical University, however, the university was granted National level status in April 2019. Today, the university is known as&nbsp;</i><b><i>Ternopil National Medical University</i></b><i>.</i></p>\r\n<p>TNMU is MCI and WHO recognized. Ternopil National Medical University is one of the top-ranking medical universities of Ukraine providing high-quality educational medical programs that meet international standards.</p>\r\n<p>The university implements European and American educational standards and integrates it into the international education and research community.</p>\r\n', '<p>The degree awarded by &nbsp;<strong>Ternopil National Medical University</strong>&nbsp;is MD (Physician) which is equivalent to MBBS in India. The course duration for MBBS in Ukraine is 5.8 years. TNMU’s degree is recognized by MCI &amp; WHO. The degree is also recognized by the International Medical Education Directory (IMED), US Education Department, and General Council Of Medicine of Great Britain.</p>\r\n<p>The total duration of the course at&nbsp;<strong>Ternopil National Medical University</strong>&nbsp;is 5.8 years, which is the same as all the other universities teaching MBBS in Ukraine.</p>\r\n<p>The first 3 years are pre-clinical where 20% of the teaching is practical training and the rest is theoretical. After this, the students appear for KROK-1 and upon clearing it, the students move to the 4th year. The final 3 years is the clinical phase where all the classes will be held in different hospitals depending on the subjects being taught to the student at the point of time.</p>\r\n<p>After completing the course, the student needs to clear KROK-2. Once this is done, the student will be awarded an MD Physician degree which is equivalent to MBBS in India. The student can then come back to India and sit for the licensing exam or go for the licensing exam of any other country.</p>\r\n', '<p><strong>Ternopil National Medical University</strong>&nbsp;hostel includes three dormitories. Each dormitory has 206 rooms and a total housing capacity of 508 persons. Each floor of the dormitory has 3 living wings. There are 3 suites, a common room, a kitchen with essential equipment, and a utility room in each wing. The suite contains 2 double occupancy rooms and 2 triple occupancy rooms, a toilet, and a shower.</p>\r\n<p>All rooms are equipped with beds, mattresses, pillow, blanket, desk, chair, central-heating facility, and suitable lighting for both study and relaxation. There are common areas where students can play and mingle. Upon the student’s arrival on campus, specific accommodations are assigned, and after a satisfactory health report.</p>\r\n<p>Ternopil National Medical University hostel features 24-hour access to security and emergency services, making it easy to get assistance when you need it. As a campus resident, you also have access to all the TNMU support services such as Campus Security Services, Counselling Services, and Health Services.</p>\r\n', '<table class=\"table-responsive table\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>YEAR</td>\r\n<td>1ST YR</td>\r\n<td>2ND</td>\r\n<td>3RD</td>\r\n<td>4TH</td>\r\n<td>5TH</td>\r\n<td>6TH</td>\r\n<td>TOTAL</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>TUITION FEES</td>\r\n<td>3800</td>\r\n<td>4100</td>\r\n<td>4100</td>\r\n<td>4300</td>\r\n<td>4300</td>\r\n<td>4500</td>\r\n<td>25100</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>HOSTEL FEES</td>\r\n<td>600</td>\r\n<td>600</td>\r\n<td>600</td>\r\n<td>600</td>\r\n<td>600</td>\r\n<td>600</td>\r\n<td>3600</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>TOTAL IN US$</td>\r\n<td>4400</td>\r\n<td>4700</td>\r\n<td>4700</td>\r\n<td>4900</td>\r\n<td>4900</td>\r\n<td>5100</td>\r\n<td>28700</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>TOTAL IN INR</td>\r\n<td>3,08,000</td>\r\n<td>3,29,000</td>\r\n<td>3,29,000</td>\r\n<td>3,43,000</td>\r\n<td>3,43,000</td>\r\n<td>3,57,000</td>\r\n<td>20,09,000</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<p>US $ 1= ₹70 has been taken as the exchange rate above. Please use the current exchange for the calculation of fees in INR.</p>', '<p>The eligibility criteria for admission in Vinnytsia National Medical University for an Indian student is as follows:</p>\r\n        \r\n<table class=\"table table-responsive\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Entrance Exam in India</td>\r\n<td>There is no entrance exam in India like IELTS/SAT, etc. NEET qualification is a must.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Age</td>\r\n<td>The student must be at least 17 years old as on 31st December of the year in which the admission is being taken.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Board</td>\r\n<td>The candidate must have completed class 12th from a regular and recognised board.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Marks in class 12th</td>\r\n<td>The student must have 50% marks individually in Physics, Chemistry and Biology in class 12th. The student must have studied Physics, Chemistry, Biology and English as compulsory subjects in 11th and 12th. The board should be a recognised one.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>NEET</td>\r\n<td>You need to qualify NEET for admission in any MCI recognised medical university in Ukraine. NEET is valid for 3 years from 2018 onwards.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Passport</td>\r\n<td>The student must hold a valid passport.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">Note:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n<li style=\"text-align: left;\" aria-level=\"1\">At the time of applying for admission letter, it is not necessary to have a passport. Admission letter can be issued if the student has a valid id proof such as Aadhar card. However, for the invitation letter and for the visa, a valid passport is required.</li>\r\n<li style=\"text-align: left;\" aria-level=\"1\">Admission is not possible in VNMU if the student has not qualified NEET.</li>\r\n</ul>', '<p>Ternopil National Medical University is recognised by the following:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul class=\"mungu-element icon-list-element \">\r\n<li><i class=\"fas fa-arrow-right\"></i>&nbsp;The Medical Council of India (MCI)</li>\r\n<li><i class=\"fas fa-arrow-right\"></i>&nbsp;World Health Organisation (WHO)</li>\r\n<li><i class=\"fas fa-arrow-right\"></i>&nbsp;ECFMG</li>\r\n<li><i class=\"fas fa-arrow-right\"></i>&nbsp;Medical Board of California</li>\r\n<li><i class=\"fas fa-arrow-right\"></i>&nbsp;Education Ministry of Ukraine</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>This means that you can appear for the licensing exams in countries such as India, the USA, UK, etc., after graduating from TNMU.</p>', '', '', 1, 1),
(3, 3, 'PUBLIC', 'M.D. PHYSICIAN', 'ENGLISH', '6 YEARS', '5000$', '<p>Danylo Halytsky &nbsp;<strong>Lviv National Medical University</strong>&nbsp;(LNMU) is one of the oldest and biggest medical educational institutions in Ukraine. It is one of the leading medical universities of the IV level of accreditation. LNMU begins from the Medical Faculty of Lviv University, which was opened on November 16, 1784, according to the privilege of the Austrian emperor Joseph II. In 2009 University celebrated its 225 anniversary.</p>\r\n<p>22 scientific schools actively function and develop in University: of obstetrics and gynecology, biochemical, hygienic, of infectious diseases, of history of medicine and pharmacy, microbiological, morphological, of neurology and neurosurgery, of oncology, of otorhinolaryngology, ophthalmological, of pathological anatomy and pathological physiology, pediatric, psychiatric, of dentistry, of internal diseases, pharmacological, physiological, of physiatry, of chemistry and pharmacy, of surgery.</p>\r\n<p>On October 21, 1998, the University was granted the name of Danylo Halytsky, after the first king of Halychyna-Ukraine. On October 21, 2003, according to the decree of the President of Ukraine, the University conferred a degree of National. One of the best things about the university is that all of its departments are in one place. This ensures that the students do not have to travel a lot during the first three years or the non-clinical phase.</p>', '<p>The degree awarded by Lviv National Medical University is MD (Physician) which is equivalent to MBBS in India. The course duration for MBBS in Ukraine is 5.8 years. VNMU’s degree is recognized by MCI &amp; WHO. The degree is also recognized by the International Medical Education Directory (IMED), US Education Department, and General Council Of Medicine of Great Britain.</p>\r\n<p>The total duration of the course at&nbsp;<em><strong>Lviv National Medical University</strong></em>&nbsp;is 5.8 years, which is the same as all the other universities teaching MBBS in Ukraine.</p>\r\n<p>The first 3 years are pre-clinical where 20% of the teaching is practical training and the rest is theoretical. After this, the students appear for KROK-1 and upon clearing it, the students move to the 4th year. The final 3 years is the clinical phase where all the classes will be held in different hospitals depending on the subjects being taught to the student at the point of time.</p>\r\n<p>After completing the course, the student needs to clear KROK-2. Once this is done, the student will be awarded an MD Physician degree which is equivalent to MBBS in India. The student can then come back to India and sit for the licensing exam or go for the licensing exam of any other country.</p>', '<p><strong>Lviv National Medical University</strong>&nbsp;provides on and off-campus hostel facilities to Indian students. The university has many hostels under its wings which are both renovated and non-renovated. Hostel-8 is the renovated hostel but is located about 4-5 km away from the main campus. The other hostels are located at the campus but are non-renovated yet are still very good.</p>\r\n<p>The hostels have a block system wherein one block houses about 10-11 students who share a common washroom/bathroom and a common kitchen. There is an availability of 2 and 3 seater rooms.</p>\r\n<p>All rooms are equipped with beds, mattresses, pillow, blanket, desk, chair, central-heating facility, and suitable lighting for both study and relaxation. There are common areas where students can play and mingle. Upon the student’s arrival on campus, specific accommodations are assigned, and after a satisfactory health report.</p>\r\n<p>LVIV National Medical University hostel features 24-hour access to security and emergency services, making it easy to get assistance when you need it. As a campus resident, you also have access to all the LNMU support services such as Campus Security Services, Counselling Servic