(6, 6, 'PUBLIC', 'M.D. PHYSICIAN', 'ENGLISH', '6 YEARS', '3900$', '<p><strong>Dnipropetrovsk State Medical Academy</strong>&nbsp;is an MCI and WHO recognized medical university in Ukraine. It was founded in 1916 and is located in the industrial capital of Ukraine, Dnipro. About half of the industries in Ukraine are set up in Dnipro. Dnipropetrovsk State Medical Academy is a state institution which comes under the Ministry of Health of Ukraine. It is a co-educational institution. The university is more than 100-year-old university having IV (the highest) level of accreditation in Ukraine. Since its existence, Dnipropetrovsk Medical Academy has trained more than 50,000 doctors, pharmacists, and nurses. International students from more than 35 different countries study here including India. DSMU is not the most popular medical college among Indian students. Between 2012-14, 60 Indian students sat for FMGE after finishing MBBS from&nbsp;<strong>Dnipro State Medical Academy</strong>, and between 2015-18, only 25 Indian students sat for FMGE.</p>', '<p>The degree awarded by&nbsp;<strong>Dnipro State Medical Academy</strong>&nbsp;is MD (Physician) which is equivalent to MBBS in India. The course duration for MBBS in Ukraine is 5.8 years. DSMA’s degree is recognized by MCI &amp; WHO. The degree is also recognized by the International Medical Education Directory (IMED), US Education Department, and General Council Of Medicine of Great Britain.</p>\r\n<p>The total duration of the course at&nbsp;<strong>Dnipro State Medical Academy&nbsp;</strong>is 5.8 years, which is the same as all the other universities teaching MBBS in Ukraine.</p>\r\n<p>The first 3 years are pre-clinical where 20% of the teaching is practical training and the rest is theoretical. After this, the students appear for KROK-1 and upon clearing it, the students move to the 4th year. The final 3 years is the clinical phase where all the classes will be held in different hospitals depending on the subjects being